                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.73/135: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-14T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 14, 1922—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9. My telegram of February 7, 4 p.m. Representative of Western Telegraph Company
                    today handed me copy of the letter that he is sending to Minister of the
                    Interior modifying first paragraph of his letter of 7th instant so as to exclude
                    all mention of Barbados, and requesting that this Embassy be informed of
                    Argentine Government’s acquiescence in waiver of special rights.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
